## 🧭 PROJECT CONTEXT

> **Most critical section. An AI that understands WHY this exists makes correct decisions autonomously.**

### Purpose
Unified firmware for ESP32-S3 that provides multiple independent modules (NFC cloning station, ultrasonic radar, web dashboard, CLI terminal) without needing to re-flash the microcontroller when switching between functions. All modules coexist and are selectable at runtime via menu or web.

### Goals
1. Modular runtime — add/use modules without re-flashing
2. Web-based remote control and monitoring
3. Real-time telemetry and historical data logging
4. NFC card cloning station (read + write MIFARE Classic 1K)
5. Ultrasonic distance radar with CLI control
6. DHT11 temperature and humidity sensor with CLI readout
7. LCD diagnostic display with rotating metrics
8. Over-the-air firmware updates (OTA)
9. Hybrid terminal (Telnet + WebSocket) for CLI access
10. Blasco AI — Gemini-powered chat assistant embedded in the dashboard (sidebar panel, streaming responses, file attachments, live telemetry context)

### Non-goals
- Mobile app (web UI is the remote interface)
- Cloud sync or remote access beyond LAN
- Multi-user support
- Support for NFC cards other than MIFARE Classic 1K
- Audio/video processing
- Real-time control loops (no hard real-time guarantees)

### Target users
Ruben Blasco Armengod (personal project). Technical (embedded/hobbyist level). Expects a development sandbox where new hardware modules can be added and tested without rebuilding the entire system.

### Key constraints
| Constraint | Detail | Impact |
|-----------|--------|--------|
| MCU | ESP32-S3 N16R8 (16MB Flash, 8MB PSRAM, 240MHz dual-core) | Firmware size limit, RAM budget for WebSocket + CSV buffer |
| Fixed pinout (defaults) | NeoPixel=GPIO48. Defaults: NFC RST=21/SS=5, HC-SR04 TRIG=15/ECHO=16, I2C SDA=8/SCL=9, SPI MOSI=11/MISO=13/CLK=18, DHT11 DATA=GPIO4. **All GPIO pins are configurable at runtime via NVS (captive portal screen 0).** | Hardware layout can be reconfigured without recompile |
| Display | LCD 16x2 I2C (addr 0x27) | Only 32 characters visible at once; **5-page rotating display** (added DHT page) |
| NFC | MFRC522 + MIFARE Classic 1K only | Cannot read/write other card types (NTAG, DESFire, etc.) |
| LED | 1x NeoPixel RGB | Single status indicator, limited to color/blink patterns |
| WiFi | Station mode + AP fallback on captive portal | Dual-mode AP+STA during initial configuration |
| WebSocket | Max 2 simultaneous clients | Hard limit; 3rd client is silently ignored |
| CSV | Auto-deletes at 8MB | Historical data loss if not exported before threshold |
| Telnet | Single session only | New connection rejected while active session exists |
| **Stack size** | **16KB per FreeRTOS task** | **Doubled from 8KB** to prevent stack overflow with ESPAsyncWebServer + ArduinoJson |
| **HMAC** | HMAC-SHA256 via mbedTLS | Cloudflare Tunnel proxy request signing/verification (x-zenith-sig, 30s window) |
| **CSV columns** | **11 columns** | Column 11 = `ultimaAlertaCritica` (col 10) — se escribe cuando seguridadNivel >= 3 |
| **CPU load** | **EMA-smoothed** (30% raw + 70% prev) | Only recalculated every 1s per core to avoid micro()-based jitter |
| **AI panel** | Google Gemini API via client-side fetch | API key stored in NVS on ESP32 (`/api/ai/key`), cached in JS variable, never in localStorage; supports gemini-2.5-flash, 2.0-flash, 1.5-flash/pro, 2.0-flash-lite; streaming SSE, file attachments, live telemetry in system prompt |
| **Cloudflare Tunnel** | Worker + Durable Object (TunnelSession) | ESP32 connects via WebSocket (`/esp-tunnel`) to Worker. Browser connects via WebSocket (`/ws`) to same DO. Worker proxies HTTP requests to ESP32 via WebSocket request/response. All browser ↔ ESP32 traffic goes through the DO singleton. |
| **Console format** | JSON `{"type":"ws_fwd","data":"..."}` | ESP32 sends console output as JSON ws_fwd messages via tunnel. Worker extracts `data` and forwards to browsers. LAN path sends raw text directly via ESPAsyncWebServer WebSocket. |
| **CSV push on connect** | Last 500 rows via WebSocket | When a browser connects via tunnel, ESP32 reads the last 500 lines of `/datos.csv` (saltando líneas viejas) y las envía como `csv_data` JSON via WebSocket. Dashboard y DB se pueblan instantáneamente. |

### Business / domain rules
- NFC cloning only works with "magic" (CUID/FUID) cards that accept block 0 writes. Standard MIFARE cards have block 0 locked at manufacturing.
- **NFC key dictionary**: 20 common keys tried per sector. Successful key per sector stored in `sectorKeyExitosas[16]`; if a previous sector key worked, it's tried first (optimization). Write uses the same stored keys.
- Menu auto-refreshes after 5 minutes of inactivity but only when clients are connected — saves LCD burn and CPU.
- CSV logging waits for NTP sync (checks year > 2000) — no valid timestamps before sync.
- Web log output is silenced for the first 30 seconds after WebSocket connects — prevents startup noise flood.
- Telnet accepts one client; any subsequent connection is rejected until the active session terminates.
- OTA protected with webPass password (same as web login) — asks for authentication before flashing.
- Two FreeRTOS tasks run at identical priority (1) — no preemption guarantees; they cooperate via vTaskDelay(10/portTICK) on Core 0, vTaskDelay(1/portTICK) on Core 1.
- I2C bus is shared between LCD and potentially other devices; protected by `i2cMutex` semaphore.
- NeoPixel brightness is fixed at 50/255 (19.6%) — changing requires recompile.
- **DHT11 polling: every 3s on Core 1** (taskCore1), not Core 0. The DHT11 native 1-Wire implementation disables interrupts (`noInterrupts()`) during the ~5ms read window — this can disrupt WiFi if the read takes too long or is called too frequently.
- **HC-SR04 is non-blocking**: ISR-based with 3-state FSM (IDLE, WAITING, ECHO), no `pulseIn()`. Returns -1 while waiting, -2 on timeout, distance in cm on success. Minimum 200ms between triggers.
- CSV cronjob: NTP-based, fires at minute 0 of every even hour (0, 2, 4… 22) with anti-duplicate guard and boot-time save.
- **LCD 5-page rotation**: cycles every 3s through TEMP+CPU, C0+C1, RAM+FLASH, WIFI+UPTIME, DHT.
- **CPU load measurement**: EMA-smoothed (30% raw / 70% previous), recalculated every 1s per core.
- **Telnet auth synchronized with webPass**: `TELNET_PASSWORD` is no longer used; Telnet authentication checks `telnetAutenticado` using `webPass` (same as web login). Inactivity timeout of 5 minutes.
- **Config page**: `/config` route added with web-based pin mapping (NFC RST/CS, HC-SR04 TRIG/ECHO, DHT DATA) and web credential change. Pins saved to NVS namespace `hwconfig`, web creds to `webcred`.
- **GPIO pin configuration is runtime**: all peripheral pins (RST_PIN, SS_PIN, TRIG_PIN, ECHO_PIN, DHT_PIN) loaded from NVS at boot, changeable via web UI or captive portal screen 0. No recompile needed.

### Assumptions
- WiFi network with known SSID and password exists and is reachable (configured in NVS).
- NFC cards presented are MIFARE Classic 1K with 4-byte UID.
- Target cards for cloning support block 0 writes (magic/CUID cards).
- I2C LCD is at address 0x27 with 16 columns and 2 rows.
- NTP servers (pool.ntp.org, time.nist.gov) are reachable from the LAN.
- ESP32-S3 has exactly 16MB Flash and 8MB PSRAM.
- Serial console operates at 115200 baud (USB CDC).
- Web browser is modern (supports ES6+, fetch, WebSocket, and Canvas).
- Device has stable USB or external 5V power.
- No other I2C devices share the bus at conflicting addresses.
- SPI bus is dedicated to MFRC522 (no other SPI devices).
- DHT11 sensor has external 4.7kΩ pull-up on DATA line (internal INPUT_PULLUP ~45kΩ is used as fallback).
- HC-SR04 ECHO pin can tolerate 5V logic (5V-tolerant GPIO on ESP32-S3).

