### Hardware connections required
```
ESP32-S3          Component (default pins — configurable via web portal and captive portal)
─────────────────────────────────────
GPIO 48     →    NeoPixel RGB DIN
GPIO 8      →    LCD SDA (I2C)
GPIO 9      →    LCD SCL (I2C)
GPIO 21     →    MFRC522 RST (default, configurable)
GPIO 5      →    MFRC522 SS/SDA (default, configurable)
GPIO 18     →    MFRC522 SCK/CLK
GPIO 13     →    MFRC522 MISO
GPIO 11     →    MFRC522 MOSI
GPIO 15     →    HC-SR04 TRIG (default, configurable)
GPIO 16     →    HC-SR04 ECHO (default, configurable)
GPIO 4      →    DHT11 DATA (default, configurable, 4.7kΩ pull-up to 3.3V recommended)
5V / 3.3V   →    Power (MCU + components)
GND         →    Common ground
Option:     →    SD Card (SPI): CS=41, CLK=40, MOSI=11, MISO=13 (#ifdef SD_CS_PIN)
```

### Setup sequence
```
1. Wire components per pin table above (defaults shown; pins can be changed later in captive portal or /config)
2. Install Arduino IDE 2.x (or PlatformIO) with ESP32-S3 board support
3. Install libraries via library manager:
   - ESPAsyncWebServer (me-no-dev)
   - MFRC522 (miguelbalboa)
   - LiquidCrystal_I2C (fdebrabander)
   - Adafruit_NeoPixel (Adafruit)
   - ArduinoJson (Benoit Blanchon)
   NOTE: DHT11 is native (no library required). SD is optional (#ifdef SD_CS_PIN).
4. Configure board: ESP32-S3 (16MB Flash, 8MB PSRAM, 240MHz)
   - USB CDC on boot: enabled
   - Flash mode: QIO 80MHz
   - Partition scheme: 16MB Flash (3MB APP/9.9MB FATFS)
5. Open main.ino in Arduino IDE
6. Select correct COM port
7. Upload firmware via USB
8. Open Serial Monitor (115200 baud) to observe boot sequence
9. First boot: LittleFS auto-formats → AP mode starts
10. Connect to WiFi "Esp32BlascoOS_Setup" → captive portal opens
11. Screen C: Configure pins and web credentials (optional — defaults work for standard wiring)
12. Screen 1: Select WiFi network → Screen 2: enter password → Screen 3: SAVE AND CONNECT
13. ESP32 reboots and connects in STA mode (AP disabled after connection)
14. Note assigned IP from Serial Monitor or LCD
15. Open browser to http://<IP> → login with configured credentials (default admin/blasco)
16. Optional: Visit /config to adjust GPIO pins or change web credentials at any time
```

